71 // Verify that the number is a positive power of 2.

73 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid packet buffer max size: " << group_name;
74 packet_buffer_max_size = kPacketBufferMaxSize;

76 return packet_buffer_max_size;

173void RtpVideoStreamReceiver2::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::SendBufferedRtcpFeedback() {
174 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
175
176 bool request_key_frame = false;
177 std::vector<uint16_t> nack_sequence_numbers;
178 absl::optional<LossNotificationState> lntf_state;
179
180 std::swap(request_key_frame, request_key_frame_);
181 std::swap(nack_sequence_numbers, nack_sequence_numbers_);
182 std::swap(lntf_state, lntf_state_);
183
184 if (lntf_state) {
185 // If either a NACK or a key frame request is sent, we should buffer
186 // the LNTF and wait for them (NACK or key frame request) to trigger
187 // the compound feedback message.
188 // Otherwise, the LNTF should be sent out immediately.
189 const bool buffering_allowed =
190 request_key_frame || !nack_sequence_numbers.empty();
191
192 loss_notification_sender_->SendLossNotification(
193 lntf_state->last_decoded_seq_num, lntf_state->last_received_seq_num,
194 lntf_state->decodability_flag, buffering_allowed);
195 }
196
197 if (request_key_frame) {
198 key_frame_request_sender_->RequestKeyFrame();
199 } else if (!nack_sequence_numbers.empty()) {
200 nack_sender_->SendNack(nack_sequence_numbers, true);
201 }
202}

366RtpVideoStreamReceiver2::ParseGenericDependenciesResult
367RtpVideoStreamReceiver2::ParseGenericDependenciesExtension(
368 const RtpPacketReceived& rtp_packet,
369 RTPVideoHeader* video_header) {
370 if (rtp_packet.HasExtension<RtpDependencyDescriptorExtension>()) {
371 webrtc::DependencyDescriptor dependency_descriptor;
372 if (!rtp_packet.GetExtension<RtpDependencyDescriptorExtension>(
373 video_structure_.get(), &dependency_descriptor)) {
374 // Descriptor is there, but failed to parse. Either it is invalid,
375 // or too old packet (after relevant video_structure_ changed),
376 // or too new packet (before relevant video_structure_ arrived).
377 // Drop such packet to be on the safe side.
378 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10342): Stash too new packet.
379 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "ssrc: " << rtp_packet.Ssrc()
380 << " Failed to parse dependency descriptor.";
381 return kDropPacket;
382 }
383 if (dependency_descriptor.attached_structure != nullptr &&
384 !dependency_descriptor.first_packet_in_frame) {
385 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "ssrc: " << rtp_packet.Ssrc()
386 << "Invalid dependency descriptor: structure "
387 "attached to non first packet of a frame.";
388 return kDropPacket;
389 }
390 video_header->is_first_packet_in_frame =
391 dependency_descriptor.first_packet_in_frame;
392 video_header->is_last_packet_in_frame =
393 dependency_descriptor.last_packet_in_frame;
394
395 int64_t frame_id =
396 frame_id_unwrapper_.Unwrap(dependency_descriptor.frame_number);
397 auto& generic_descriptor_info = video_header->generic.emplace();
398 generic_descriptor_info.frame_id = frame_id;
399 generic_descriptor_info.spatial_index =
400 dependency_descriptor.frame_dependencies.spatial_id;
401 generic_descriptor_info.temporal_index =
402 dependency_descriptor.frame_dependencies.temporal_id;
403 for (int fdiff : dependency_descriptor.frame_dependencies.frame_diffs) {
404 generic_descriptor_info.dependencies.push_back(frame_id - fdiff);
405 }
406 generic_descriptor_info.decode_target_indications =
407 dependency_descriptor.frame_dependencies.decode_target_indications;
408 if (dependency_descriptor.resolution) {
409 video_header->width = dependency_descriptor.resolution->Width();
410 video_header->height = dependency_descriptor.resolution->Height();
411 }
412
413 // FrameDependencyStructure is sent in dependency descriptor of the first
414 // packet of a key frame and required for parsed dependency descriptor in
415 // all the following packets until next key frame.
416 // Save it if there is a (potentially) new structure.
417 if (dependency_descriptor.attached_structure) {
418 RTC_DCHECK(dependency_descriptor.first_packet_in_frame);
419 if (video_structure_frame_id_ > frame_id) {
420 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
421 << "Arrived key frame with id " << frame_id << " and structure id "
422 << dependency_descriptor.attached_structure->structure_id
423 << " is older than the latest received key frame with id "
424 << *video_structure_frame_id_ << " and structure id "
425 << video_structure_->structure_id;
426 return kDropPacket;
427 }
428 video_structure_ = std::move(dependency_descriptor.attached_structure);
429 video_structure_frame_id_ = frame_id;
430 video_header->frame_type = VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
431 } else {
432 video_header->frame_type = VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta;
433 }
434 return kHasGenericDescriptor;
435 }
436
437 RtpGenericFrameDescriptor generic_frame_descriptor;
438 if (!rtp_packet.GetExtension<RtpGenericFrameDescriptorExtension00>(
439 &generic_frame_descriptor)) {
440 return kNoGenericDescriptor;
441 }
442
443 video_header->is_first_packet_in_frame =
444 generic_frame_descriptor.FirstPacketInSubFrame();
445 video_header->is_last_packet_in_frame =
446 generic_frame_descriptor.LastPacketInSubFrame();
447
448 if (generic_frame_descriptor.FirstPacketInSubFrame()) {
449 video_header->frame_type =
450 generic_frame_descriptor.FrameDependenciesDiffs().empty()
451 ? VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey
452 : VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta;
453
454 auto& generic_descriptor_info = video_header->generic.emplace();
455 int64_t frame_id =
456 frame_id_unwrapper_.Unwrap(generic_frame_descriptor.FrameId());
457 generic_descriptor_info.frame_id = frame_id;
458 generic_descriptor_info.spatial_index =
459 generic_frame_descriptor.SpatialLayer();
460 generic_descriptor_info.temporal_index =
461 generic_frame_descriptor.TemporalLayer();
462 for (uint16_t fdiff : generic_frame_descriptor.FrameDependenciesDiffs()) {
463 generic_descriptor_info.dependencies.push_back(frame_id - fdiff);
464 }
465 }
466 video_header->width = generic_frame_descriptor.Width();
467 video_header->height = generic_frame_descriptor.Height();
468 return kHasGenericDescriptor;
469}

471void RtpVideoStreamReceiver2::OnReceivedPayloadData(
472 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer codec_payload,
473 const RtpPacketReceived& rtp_packet,
474 const RTPVideoHeader& video) {
475 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
476
477 auto packet =
478 std::make_unique<video_coding::PacketBuffer::Packet>(rtp_packet, video);
479
480 int64_t unwrapped_rtp_seq_num =
481 rtp_seq_num_unwrapper_.Unwrap(rtp_packet.SequenceNumber());
482 auto& packet_info =
483 packet_infos_
484 .emplace(
485 unwrapped_rtp_seq_num,
486 RtpPacketInfo(
487 rtp_packet.Ssrc(), rtp_packet.Csrcs(), rtp_packet.Timestamp(),
488 /*audio_level=*/absl::nullopt,
489 rtp_packet.GetExtension<AbsoluteCaptureTimeExtension>(),
490 /*receive_time_ms=*/clock_->CurrentTime()))
491 .first->second;
492
493 // Try to extrapolate absolute capture time if it is missing.
494 packet_info.set_absolute_capture_time(
495 absolute_capture_time_receiver_.OnReceivePacket(
496 AbsoluteCaptureTimeReceiver::GetSource(packet_info.ssrc(),
497 packet_info.csrcs()),
498 packet_info.rtp_timestamp(),
499 // Assume frequency is the same one for all video frames.
500 kVideoPayloadTypeFrequency, packet_info.absolute_capture_time()));
501
502 RTPVideoHeader& video_header = packet->video_header;
503 video_header.rotation = kVideoRotation_0;
504 video_header.content_type = VideoContentType::UNSPECIFIED;
505 video_header.video_timing.flags = VideoSendTiming::kInvalid;
506 video_header.is_last_packet_in_frame |= rtp_packet.Marker();
507
508 if (const auto* vp9_header =
509 absl::get_if<RTPVideoHeaderVP9>(&video_header.video_type_header)) {
510 video_header.is_last_packet_in_frame |= vp9_header->end_of_frame;
511 video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame |= vp9_header->beginning_of_frame;
512 }
513
514 rtp_packet.GetExtension<VideoOrientation>(&video_header.rotation);
515 rtp_packet.GetExtension<VideoContentTypeExtension>(
516 &video_header.content_type);
517 rtp_packet.GetExtension<VideoTimingExtension>(&video_header.video_timing);
518 if (forced_playout_delay_max_ms_ && forced_playout_delay_min_ms_) {
519 video_header.playout_delay.max_ms = *forced_playout_delay_max_ms_;
520 video_header.playout_delay.min_ms = *forced_playout_delay_min_ms_;
521 } else {
522 rtp_packet.GetExtension<PlayoutDelayLimits>(&video_header.playout_delay);
523 }
524
525 ParseGenericDependenciesResult generic_descriptor_state =
526 ParseGenericDependenciesExtension(rtp_packet, &video_header);
527
528 if (!rtp_packet.recovered()) {
529 UpdatePacketReceiveTimestamps(
530 rtp_packet, video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey);
531 }
532
533 if (generic_descriptor_state == kDropPacket)
534 return;
535
536 // Color space should only be transmitted in the last packet of a frame,
537 // therefore, neglect it otherwise so that last_color_space_ is not reset by
538 // mistake.
539 if (video_header.is_last_packet_in_frame) {
540 video_header.color_space = rtp_packet.GetExtension<ColorSpaceExtension>();
541 if (video_header.color_space ||
542 video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
543 // Store color space since it's only transmitted when changed or for key
544 // frames. Color space will be cleared if a key frame is transmitted
545 // without color space information.
546 last_color_space_ = video_header.color_space;
547 } else if (last_color_space_) {
548 video_header.color_space = last_color_space_;
549 }
550 }
551 video_header.video_frame_tracking_id =
552 rtp_packet.GetExtension<VideoFrameTrackingIdExtension>();
553
554 if (loss_notification_controller_) {
555 if (rtp_packet.recovered()) {
556 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10336): Implement support for reordering.
557 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
558 << "LossNotificationController does not support reordering.";
559 } else if (generic_descriptor_state == kNoGenericDescriptor) {
560 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "LossNotificationController requires generic "
561 "frame descriptor, but it is missing.";
562 } else {
563 if (video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame) {
564 RTC_DCHECK(video_header.generic);
565 LossNotificationController::FrameDetails frame;
566 frame.is_keyframe =
567 video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
568 frame.frame_id = video_header.generic->frame_id;
569 frame.frame_dependencies = video_header.generic->dependencies;
570 loss_notification_controller_->OnReceivedPacket(
571 rtp_packet.SequenceNumber(), &frame);
572 } else {
573 loss_notification_controller_->OnReceivedPacket(
574 rtp_packet.SequenceNumber(), nullptr);
575 }
576 }
577 }
578
579 if (nack_module_) {

617 case video_coding::H264SpsPpsTracker::kInsert:

733void RtpVideoStreamReceiver2::OnInsertedPacket(
734 video_coding::PacketBuffer::InsertResult result) {
735 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
736 video_coding::PacketBuffer::Packet* first_packet = nullptr;
737 int max_nack_count;
738 int64_t min_recv_time;
739 int64_t max_recv_time;
740 std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t>> payloads;
741 RtpPacketInfos::vector_type packet_infos;
742
743 bool frame_boundary = true;
744 for (auto& packet : result.packets) {
745 // PacketBuffer promisses frame boundaries are correctly set on each
746 // packet. Document that assumption with the DCHECKs.
747 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame_boundary, packet->is_first_packet_in_frame());
748 int64_t unwrapped_rtp_seq_num =
749 rtp_seq_num_unwrapper_.Unwrap(packet->seq_num);
750 RTC_DCHECK(packet_infos_.count(unwrapped_rtp_seq_num) > 0);
751 RtpPacketInfo& packet_info = packet_infos_[unwrapped_rtp_seq_num];
752 if (packet->is_first_packet_in_frame()) {
753 first_packet = packet.get();
754 max_nack_count = packet->times_nacked;
755 min_recv_time = packet_info.receive_time().ms();
756 max_recv_time = packet_info.receive_time().ms();
757 payloads.clear();
758 packet_infos.clear();
759 } else {
760 max_nack_count = std::max(max_nack_count, packet->times_nacked);
761 min_recv_time = std::min(min_recv_time, packet_info.receive_time().ms());
762 max_recv_time = std::max(max_recv_time, packet_info.receive_time().ms());
763 }
764 payloads.emplace_back(packet->video_payload);
765 packet_infos.push_back(packet_info);
766
767 frame_boundary = packet->is_last_packet_in_frame();
768 if (packet->is_last_packet_in_frame()) {
769 auto depacketizer_it = payload_type_map_.find(first_packet->payload_type);
770 RTC_CHECK(depacketizer_it != payload_type_map_.end());
771
772 rtc::scoped_refptr<EncodedImageBuffer> bitstream =
773 depacketizer_it->second->AssembleFrame(payloads);
774 if (!bitstream) {
775 // Failed to assemble a frame. Discard and continue.
776 continue;
777 }
778
779 const video_coding::PacketBuffer::Packet& last_packet = *packet;
780 OnAssembledFrame(std::make_unique<RtpFrameObject>(
781 first_packet->seq_num, //
782 last_packet.seq_num, //
783 last_packet.marker_bit, //
784 max_nack_count, //
785 min_recv_time, //
786 max_recv_time, //
787 first_packet->timestamp, //
788 ntp_estimator_.Estimate(first_packet->timestamp), //
789 last_packet.video_header.video_timing, //
790 first_packet->payload_type, //
791 first_packet->codec(), //
792 last_packet.video_header.rotation, //
793 last_packet.video_header.content_type, //
794 first_packet->video_header, //
795 last_packet.video_header.color_space, //
796 RtpPacketInfos(std::move(packet_infos)), //
797 std::move(bitstream)));
798 }
799 }
800 RTC_DCHECK(frame_boundary);
801 if (result.buffer_cleared) {
802 last_received_rtp_system_time_.reset();
803 last_received_keyframe_rtp_system_time_.reset();
804 last_received_keyframe_rtp_timestamp_.reset();
805 packet_infos_.clear();
806 RequestKeyFrame();
807 }

810void RtpVideoStreamReceiver2::OnAssembledFrame(
811 std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject> frame) {
812 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
813 RTC_DCHECK(frame);
814
815#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
816 static const unsigned MaxFrameDelayCount = 3;
817 static const unsigned TimeStampQueueDurationInMs = 2000;
818 static const unsigned OneSecondInMs = 1000;
819 // FIXME: Consider using MovingAverage instead.
820 ++frameCount_;
821
822 auto frameTime = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
823 auto lastFrameTime = observedFrameTimeStamps_.empty() ? frameTime : observedFrameTimeStamps_.back();
824
825 if (observedFrameRate_) {
826 auto delay = frameTime - lastFrameTime;
827 if (delay > (MaxFrameDelayCount * OneSecondInMs / observedFrameRate_)) {
828 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "RtpVideoStreamReceiver::OnAssembledFrame at " << frameTime << ", previous frame was at " << lastFrameTime << ", observed frame rate is " << observedFrameRate_ << ", delay since last frame is " << (frameTime - lastFrameTime) << " ms, frame count is " << frameCount_ << ", size is " << frame->EncodedImage().size() << ", frame reception duration is " << (frame->video_timing().receive_finish_ms - frame->video_timing().receive_start_ms) << " ms, " << " observed samples count is " << observedFrameTimeStamps_.size() << ", observed samples duration is " << (observedFrameTimeStamps_.back() - observedFrameTimeStamps_.front());
829 }
830 }
831
832 observedFrameTimeStamps_.push_back(frameTime);
833 while (observedFrameTimeStamps_.front() <= (frameTime - TimeStampQueueDurationInMs))
834 observedFrameTimeStamps_.pop_front();
835
836 auto queueDuration = frameTime - observedFrameTimeStamps_.front();
837 if (queueDuration > OneSecondInMs)
838 observedFrameRate_ = observedFrameTimeStamps_.size() * OneSecondInMs / queueDuration;
839#endif
840
841 const absl::optional<RTPVideoHeader::GenericDescriptorInfo>& descriptor =
842 frame->GetRtpVideoHeader().generic;
843
844 if (loss_notification_controller_ && descriptor) {
845 loss_notification_controller_->OnAssembledFrame(
846 frame->first_seq_num(), descriptor->frame_id,
847 absl::c_linear_search(descriptor->decode_target_indications,
848 DecodeTargetIndication::kDiscardable),
849 descriptor->dependencies);
850 }
851
852 // If frames arrive before a key frame, they would not be decodable.
853 // In that case, request a key frame ASAP.
854 if (!has_received_frame_) {
855 if (frame->FrameType() != VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
856 // |loss_notification_controller_|, if present, would have already
857 // requested a key frame when the first packet for the non-key frame
858 // had arrived, so no need to replicate the request.
859 if (!loss_notification_controller_) {
860 RequestKeyFrame();
861 }
862 }
863 has_received_frame_ = true;
864 }
865
866 // Reset |reference_finder_| if |frame| is new and the codec have changed.
867 if (current_codec_) {
868 bool frame_is_newer =
869 AheadOf(frame->Timestamp(), last_assembled_frame_rtp_timestamp_);
870
871 if (frame->codec_type() != current_codec_) {
872 if (frame_is_newer) {
873 // When we reset the |reference_finder_| we don't want new picture ids
874 // to overlap with old picture ids. To ensure that doesn't happen we
875 // start from the |last_completed_picture_id_| and add an offset in case
876 // of reordering.
877 reference_finder_ = std::make_unique<RtpFrameReferenceFinder>(
878 this,
879 last_completed_picture_id_ + std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max());
880 current_codec_ = frame->codec_type();
881 } else {
882 // Old frame from before the codec switch, discard it.
883 return;
884 }
885 }
886
887 if (frame_is_newer) {
888 last_assembled_frame_rtp_timestamp_ = frame->Timestamp();
889 }
890 } else {
891 current_codec_ = frame->codec_type();
892 last_assembled_frame_rtp_timestamp_ = frame->Timestamp();
893 }
894
895 if (buffered_frame_decryptor_ != nullptr) {
896 buffered_frame_decryptor_->ManageEncryptedFrame(std::move(frame));
897 } else if (frame_transformer_delegate_) {
898 frame_transformer_delegate_->TransformFrame(std::move(frame));
899 } else {
900 reference_finder_->ManageFrame(std::move(frame));
901 }
902}
